    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="308"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/83</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Sharp</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3231</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In compliance with the Department’s No. 1051 of
                    April 25 directing me to inform the French authorities of the citizenship of
                    Armand Robert Garrot [etc.] I communicated with the Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs.</p>
                <p>The Minister has just replied that according to French law, Mr. Garrot is French,
                    being born abroad of a French father, and that the naturalization of the father,
                    having been made after the birth of the son, does not modify his origin.</p>
                <p>The Minister’s note, a copy and translation of which is enclosed,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d308fn2">Not printed.</note> states that it is not possible to
                    release Mr. Garrot from military service for which he is held in France.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Ambassador: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Woods Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
